    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-01-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-01-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="172"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d172">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851T.48/7</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Secretary of State</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-01-18">January 18,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The French Ambassador<note n="32" xml:id="d172fn32">Gaston Henry-Haye.</note>
                    called at his request. He brought up the question of cooperation by this
                    Government in furnishing relief for North Africa in the form of sugar, gasoline
                    and oil, et cetera. I replied that we were giving this matter attention each day
                    and had accumulated most of the facts we desired as a basis for a final
                    decision. I added that there was nothing I could say until we had obtained and
                    developed all the facts, which should be very soon. He seemed to be satisfied
                    with this.</p>
                <p>In connection with the foregoing he handed me the accompanying statement (copy
                        attached)<note n="33" xml:id="d172fn33">Not printed.</note> itemizing goods
                    which are being interrupted in their shipment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>C[<hi rend="smallcaps">ordell</hi>] H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >ull</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
